cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper describes a segmentation method for biological structures in fluorescence microscopy images using convolutional neural networks, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of data augmentation and inhomogeneity correction also suggests a focus on machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the development of a new segmentation method, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or medical imaging (cs.MM).
